newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-AUSTRALIAN P-NOTES-Tenders total A$57.2 mln.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-AUSTRALIAN P-NOTES-Tenders total A$57.2 mln.

text.p: Australian commercial paper issuers sold A$57.2 million worth of promissory notes via tenders on Wednesday.
McDonald's Corp's Australian unit made the largest issue on the day, selling A$30 million of one-month paper at three to four basis points over the corresponding bank bill mid-rate.

Discount securities dealers said short end dealings over the morning had been volatile after the Reserve Bank of Australia's decision to leave monetary policy unchanged amid market speculation of a rate cut.
At 11.35 a.m. (0035 GMT), March 90-day bank bill futures
were trading at 94.34, down three points.

* = Amounts in A$ millions. ! = deferred settlement.
Note: BBSW column shows bank bill mid-rate closest to maturity of issue. Tender results supplied by Commonwealth Bank of Australia, National Australia Bank and Westpac Banking Corp.
